ce:section.ce:para:
In the experiment of standard recovery, PE MPs were added to the river water sample, indicating the sensor had application prospect in practical detection and analysis (Fig. 4
                         and Table 1
                        ). In addition, recent centralized microplastic sensors and microplastic fluorescence detection assays were briefly summarized and compared (Table S6). Our sensors achieve fast and easy detection of PE MPs, with obvious fluorescence “turned on” in a short time. The quantitative analysis of PE MPs with low concentration and low mass was realized, which provided a new scheme for the quantitative measurement of PE MPs in fluorescence method.
